<h3>From Philosophy to Architecture</h3>

<p>
Atmakosh translates philosophical principles into concrete system design.
The architecture is layered, auditable, and modular.
</p>

<h4>Layer 1 — Cognition Engine</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Core LLM for language, reasoning, and analysis</li>
  <li>Retrieval-augmented generation for factual grounding</li>
  <li>Transparent reasoning traces where appropriate</li>
</ul>

<h4>Layer 2 — Consciousness Alignment Layer</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Ethical constraint modules (dharma, ahimsa, satya)</li>
  <li>Long-term impact modeling (people, systems, reputation)</li>
  <li>Value-aware trade-off articulation</li>
</ul>

<h4>Layer 3 — Integrative Intelligence Layer</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Synthesis across multiple perspectives</li>
  <li>Refusal or deferral in ambiguous or harmful scenarios</li>
  <li>Encouragement of insight, reflection, and responsibility</li>
</ul>

<p>
This layered design ensures Atmakosh remains powerful,
yet restrained — capable, yet accountable.
</p>
